"Behaviour": "Indicates that there was not enough disk space to store the image. Error message is output to the Service Log. The SOP Instance will not be saved."
"Indicates that rejection note was already received."

"Error Comment": "Subsequent occurrence of rejected Object [uid={SOP Instance UID}
column7: "Indicates that there was a subsequent occurrence of a rejected object during store operation."

"Error Comment": "Failed to reject Instance[uid={SOP Instance UID}] - no such Instance."
"Behaviour": "Indicates that one or more objects were not previously stored in archive to be rejected."

"Error Comment": "Failed to reject Instance[uid={SOP Instance UID}] - class-instance conflict."
"Behaviour": "Indicates that there was a conflict in SOP Class UIDs of object (between that of the previously received object and the one referenced in the current rejection note) to be rejected."

"Error Comment": "Failed to reject Instance[uid={SOP Instance UID}] - already rejected."
"Behaviour": "Indicates that the rejected object was already rejected."

"Further Meaning": "Rejection for Retention Policy Expired not Authorized"
"Error Comment": "Rejection for Retention Policy Expired not authorized."
"Behaviour": "Indicates that rejection of objects with type as Retention Expired  are not allowed by LDAP configuration."

"Further Meaning": "Retention Period of Study not yet Expired"
"Error Comment": "Retention Period of Study not yet expired."
"Behaviour": "Indicates that rejection of objects is not allowed as Study Retention Period has not expired yet."

"Further Meaning": "No Patient ID (from trusted Assigning Authority) in object."
"Error Comment": "Storage denied as Patient ID missing in object."
"Behaviour": "Indicates that the Patient ID is missing in the object or is not from a trusted Assigning Authority."

"Error Comment": "Patient ID in incoming object does not match with that of patient associated with study."
"Behaviour": "Indicates that the Patient ID in incoming object does not match with that of patient associated with study."

"Error Comment": "Patient differs from previous received object in attribute {Keyword <Tag>}."
"Behaviour": "Indicates that the Patient in incoming object has differing attributes with that of same patient associated with previous received object."
"Indicates that no bulkdata file was sent in the request body."

"Error Comment": "Study Instance UID differs from Accepted Study Instance UID."
"Behaviour": "Indicates that Accepted Study Instance UID varies from the Study Instance UID received in the request body."
"Indicates that non(-valid) DICOM stream was received in the request body."

"Further Meaning": "Data Set does not match SOP Class"
"Behaviour": "Indicates that the Data Set does not encode a valid instance of the SOP Class specified. This status is returned if the DICOM Object stream can be successfully parsed but does not contain values for one or more mandatory Elements of the SOP Class. The STORAGE-SCP AE does not perform a comprehensive check
column7: as it only checks a subset of required Elements. In addition
column8: if the SOP Class is for a type of image but the SOP Instance does not contain values necessary for its display then this status is returned. Error message is output to the Service Log. The system can be configured to temporarily save such Data Sets in order to aid problem diagnosis."

"Behaviour": "Indicates that the STORAGE-SCP AE cannot parse the Data Set into Elements. Error message is output to the Service Log. The system can be configured to temporarily save such Data Sets in order to aid problem diagnosis."
"Indicates that the STORAGE-SCP AE failed to parse received object."
"Indicates that one or more Element values were coerced. Refer to the Attributes defined in Annex for a list of those that can be coerced. Note that return of this status is disabled by default
column7: as some SCUs treat it as an Error code rather than a Warning."
